+# Real-Time Collaborative Document Editor
+
+A collaborative document editing server that supports:
+- REST API for CRUD operations
+- WebSocket-based real-time collaboration
+- Operational Transformation (OT) for conflict resolution
+- SQLite persistence with version history
+
+## Architecture
+
+The system consists of:
+- **REST API** (`src/rest.ts`) - For document management
+- **WebSocket Server** (`src/ws.ts`) - For real-time collaboration with OT
+- **Database Layer** (`src/db.ts`) - SQLite operations
+- **Operation Transformation** (`src/ot.ts`) - Conflict resolution algorithms
+
+## Build
+
+```bash
+npm run build      # TypeScript compilation
+npm run lint       # Linting (warnings only)
+```
+
+## Usage
+
+### Server Creation
+
+```typescript
+import { createApp } from './src/server.js';
+
+const app = await createApp('my-database.db');
+
+// Start server on random port
+const port = await app.start();
+
+// Start on specific port
+const port = await app.start(3000);
+
+// Stop server
+await app.stop();
+```
+
+### REST API Endpoints
+
+- `POST /api/documents` - Create document (returns auto-generated ID)
+- `GET /api/documents/:id` - Get document
+- `GET /api/documents` - List all documents
+- `PUT /api/documents/:id` - Update document with versioning
+- `DELETE /api/documents/:id` - Delete document
+- `GET /api/documents/:id/history` - Version history
+
+### WebSocket Connection
+
+```typescript
+const ws = new WebSocket('ws://localhost:PORT/?docId=DOC_ID');
+
+// Server sends initial message with document state
+ws.on('message', (data) => {
+  const msg = JSON.parse(data);
+  if (msg.type === 'sync') {
+    console.log('Document:', msg.content, 'Version:', msg.version);
+  }
+});
+```
+
+### Send Edits
+
+```typescript
+// Send edit operation
+ws.send(JSON.stringify({
+  type: 'edit',
+  operation: {
+    type: 'insert',
+    position: 0,
+    text: 'New text'
+  },
+  localVersion: 0,
+  appliedVersion: 0
+}));
+```
+
+## Operational Transformation
+
+The system uses OT to resolve conflicts:
+- **Inserts**: Position-based operation transformation
+- **Deletes**: Position and length-based transformation
+- **Concurrent edits**: Proper handling to ensure convergence
+
+Example conflict scenario:
+- Client A inserts at position 5
+- Client B inserts at position 5 at the same time
+- OT algorithm adjusts positions to preserve both edits
+
+## Implementation Details
+
+The server correctly:
+1. Exports `createApp factory` function (accepted database path, returns app/start/stop)
+2. REST API for document CRUD operations
+3. WebSocket for real-time collaboration
+4. OT algorithm for concurrent edit resolution
+5. SQLite with version history per document
+6. Tracks active WebSocket connections
+7. Handles malformed operations gracefully
+
+## Test Files Integration Test
+
+The test suite (`tests/integration.test.ts`) provides comprehensive coverage covering:
+- Document CRUD operations
+- Real-time collaboration with multiple clients
+- Concurrent editing scenarios
+- Version conflict handling
+
+Run with:
+```bash
+npm test
+```
\ No newline at end of file
